{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.4",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 4 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:1",
      "text": "Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend, that you may know prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:2",
      "text": "I will give you a good gift, forsake not my law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:3",
      "text": "For I also was my father's son, tender, and as an only son in the sight of my mother:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:4",
      "text": "And he taught me, and said: Let thy heart receive my words, keep my commandments, and thou shalt live.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:5",
      "text": "Get wisdom, get prudence: forget not, neither decline from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:6",
      "text": "Forsake her not, and she shall keep thee: love her, and she shall preserve thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:7",
      "text": "The beginning of wisdom, get wisdom, and with all thy possession purchase prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:8",
      "text": "Take hold on her, and she shall exalt thee: thou shalt be glorified by her, when thou shalt embrace her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:9",
      "text": "She shall give to thy head increase of graces, and protect thee with a noble crown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:10",
      "text": "Hear, O my son, and receive my words, that years of life may be multiplied to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:11",
      "text": "I will shew thee the way of wisdom, I will lead thee by the paths of equity:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:12",
      "text": "Which when thou shalt have entered, thy steps shall not be straitened, and when thou runnest, thou shalt not meet a stumblingblock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:13",
      "text": "Take hold on instruction, leave it not: keep it, because it is thy life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:14",
      "text": "Be not delighted in the paths of the wicked, neither let the way of evil men please thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:15",
      "text": "Flee from it, pass not by it: go aside, and forsake it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:16",
      "text": "For they sleep not, except they have done evil: and their sleep is taken away unless they have made some to fall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:17",
      "text": "They eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:18",
      "text": "But the path of the just, as a shining light, goeth forwards, and increaseth even to perfect day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:19",
      "text": "The way of the wicked is darksome: they know not where they fall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:20",
      "text": "My son, hearken to my words, and incline thy ear to my sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:21",
      "text": "Let them not depart from thy eyes, keep them in the midst of thy heart:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:22",
      "text": "For they are life to those that find them, and health to all flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:23",
      "text": "With all watchfulness keep thy heart, because life issueth out from it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:24",
      "text": "Remove from thee a froward mouth, and let detracting lips be far from thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:25",
      "text": "Let thy eyes look straight on, and let thy eyelids go before thy steps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:26",
      "text": "Make straight the path for thy feet, and all thy ways shall be established.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.4.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:27",
      "text": "Decline not to the right hand, nor to the left: turn away thy foot from evil. For the Lord knoweth the ways that are on the right hand: but those are perverse which are on the left hand. But he will make thy courses straight, he will bring forward thy ways in peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
